<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="46" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,151,575]" pageId="7" pageNumber="46">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,151,176]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="46" reason="1">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species is close to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Watson. So" authorityYear="1957" box="[554,642,152,176]" class="Insecta" family="Drepanidae" genus="Tridrepana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="finita">
<emphasis box="[554,642,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="46">T. finita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
on the wing pattern but larger. Two brownish black spots are present under M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[246,254,203,217]" fontSize="6" pageId="7" pageNumber="46">3</subScript>
and CuA 
<subScript attach="left" box="[362,370,203,217]" fontSize="6" pageId="7" pageNumber="46">1</subScript>
near the lower angle of the cell on the forewing, instead of big grayish brown patches centered by dark spots as in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Watson. So" authorityYear="1957" box="[371,459,227,251]" class="Insecta" family="Drepanidae" genus="Tridrepana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="finita">
<emphasis box="[371,459,227,251]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="46">T. finita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; the postmedial line is thin and deeply wavy, nearly continuous. In the male genitalia, the two lobes of the uncus are triangular, with the lateral margins oblique, while in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Watson. So" authorityYear="1957" box="[1088,1175,263,287]" class="Insecta" family="Drepanidae" genus="Tridrepana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="finita">
<emphasis box="[1088,1175,263,287]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="46">T. finita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the lobes of the uncus are nearly quadrate, with lateral sides nearly erect.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
